{"key":"post-16390213","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16390213</id>\n<content>Using &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf cakes&lt;/a&gt; to spawn to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Horse-Manure-Substrate&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;horse manure&lt;/a&gt; is a tried and true method.&amp;nbsp; It works fine.&amp;nbsp; You might have more spawn using grain jars, but that's in the future.&amp;nbsp; If you want to experiment, make a tray and use half your jars as spawn and the other half to fruit as cakes.&amp;nbsp; If you spawn cakes, knock them out of the jars and rinse well under a faucet of running water first to get all the verm filter off because that's where the contaminants are hiding.&amp;nbsp; Then break them up and mix with your pasteurized manure.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Get field aged and dry manure from the pasture, not what they sweep out of the barns.&amp;nbsp; It should look like what you see in the video, and will have no smell.&amp;nbsp; Bear in mind, that's just a short clip from the manure video.&amp;nbsp; The full tek is on the DVD or &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Download&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;Let's Grow Mushrooms download.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16390343</next>\n<prev>16390156</prev>\n<first>16390101</first>\n<last>16405766</last>\n<when>1339874919</when>\n<utime>06/16/12 10:28 PM</utime>\n</post>"}